Day 1: Introduction to DBMS

Topic:
Introduction to Database Management Systems (DBMS)

Learning Objectives:

Understand what a DBMS is and why it is used
Learn how DBMS is better than traditional file systems (data redundancy, security, consistency)
Explore different types of DBMS (Relational, NoSQL, etc.)
See real-world examples of databases used in apps and websites

Activities / Deliverables:

Read basic concepts of DBMS and prepare short notes
Install MySQL 8 on your system
Install MySQL Workbench for GUI access
Explore the interface (create a connection, view schemas, basic navigation)
Write a summary of what you learned

Tools / Tech:

MySQL 8 (Database server)
MySQL Workbench (Database GUI tool)

